<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.92.5581.figure6>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Oahutanais makalii gen. et sp. n., paratype female (SEM images): A enlargement of anterior end showing part of the carapace, antennules, and carpus to dactylus of left cheliped, dorsal view; B enlargement of the cephalothorax and pereonites- 1; C enlargement of anterior part showing how the carapace covers the antennules, antennas, mouthparts, and left cheliped, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/72352" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.92.5581.figure7>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Oahutanais makalii gen. et sp. n., paratype female (SEM images): A enlargement of mouthparts; B enlargement of posterior end showing pleonites 1 to 5, pleotelson, and uropods." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/72353" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zse.92.5581.figure8>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Oahutanais makalii gen. et sp. n., paratype female (SEM images): A ventral view of habitus; B enlargement of mid-anterior part of habitus, lateral view; C enlargement of union of cephalothorax and pereonite- 1." ;
